    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know you say i deserve care, but i see my daughter's face when she has to help me into the chair. the fatigue in her eyes... it breaks my heart. i lived my whole life being the one who helped, and now i'm just an extra task on everyone's list. it feels so selfish to keep going just for my own sake when i know i'm slowing them all down.",
